title: Webster Thomas cheerleaders place at competition
text: Webster Thomas cheerleaders place at competition Comment By Submitted to the Post Webster Post By Submitted to the Post Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 9:31 AM Updated at 9:31 AM By Submitted to the Post Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 9:31 AM Webster, N.Y. Two Webster Thomas cheerleaders took the stage and shone Oct. 7 at this year’s Eddie Meath All-Star Cheer Competition. Alyssa Bowen took eighth place, and Emma Schaefer placed 15th. Both girls created their own individual performance and choreography to music and performed solo. Both girls will cheer at the Eddie Meath Charity football game in July in efforts to raise money for the Golisano Children’s Hospital. Senior Alyssa Bowen began cheerleading as an All Star Cheerleader at the age of 6. She competed at Worlds for the past two years. She began cheerleading for Webster Thomas in seventh grade and made varsity as a freshman. Last year, Alyssa was chosen for the First-Team All-County Cheer Award. In her junior year, she received the Blue and Gold Award from her coaches. Senior Emma Schaefer began cheerleading in Webster’s Junior Titans program in fourth grade. She made the Titan freshman team in seventh grade and has shone on Webster’s varsity team for the past three years. In her junior year, she cheered for Fame All Stars and won U.S. Finals. She was chosen for the Second-Team All-County last Fall and First-Team All-County last winter. By Submitted to the Post Webster Post By Submitted to the Post Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 9:31 AM
